<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

  <title>Privacy Policy | CareerTrack</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/responsive.css" />
</head>
<body>

<%- include("./partials/public-navbar") %>

<main>

  <section class="legal-hero">
    <p class="tagline">Data Protection</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how CareerTrack handles user data and application information.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-container">

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        CareerTrack may collect basic user information such as name, email address,
        profile details, job application records, interview dates, notes and status updates.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        The information is used to help users manage job and internship applications,
        display dashboard analytics, track progress, and provide reminders or notifications.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>3. Application Data</h2>
      <p>
        Users can store company names, job roles, locations, application status, applied dates,
        interview dates, source details and personal notes related to their career applications.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>4. Local Storage Usage</h2>
      <p>
        The frontend version may use browser localStorage to temporarily store application
        data for testing. In the full-stack version, this data will be stored securely in a database.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>5. Database Storage</h2>
      <p>
        In the backend version, user data and application records will be stored using MongoDB.
        Access to user-specific data will be protected through authentication and authorization.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>6. Authentication</h2>
      <p>
        CareerTrack will use secure login methods such as hashed passwords and JWT-based
        authentication to protect user accounts and prevent unauthorized access.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>7. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        CareerTrack does not sell or share user information with third parties. User data is
        intended only for personal career tracking and platform functionality.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>8. Email Notifications</h2>
      <p>
        If email notification features are enabled, CareerTrack may use the user's email address
        to send interview reminders, follow-up alerts or account-related messages.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>9. User Control</h2>
      <p>
        Users may add, update or delete their application records. In the full-stack version,
        users will be able to manage profile information and account-related data.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-card">
      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions, users can contact the CareerTrack support team through
        the Contact page.
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>

</main>

<%- include("./partials/footer") %>

<script src="js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>